[We are most grateful for this comprehensive report. Some clarifications
are necessary. The sensitivity of virus isolation, under optimal
conditions (properly collected specimens, tested by knowledgeable
technicians by accepted techniques), is not low; it is high. Low
sensitivity speaks for itself. Indeed, infection with VEE virus is one of
the easiest of all viruses to diagnose; antibody titers are high, no matter
what test one uses (except, perhaps, agar gel diffusion) and viremia titers
may approach 10 logs in mosquitoes, 6-7 logs (as I recall) in equids.
Obviously, in this outbreak the effects of vaccination are clear. Such
vaccination, however, produces antibody to VEE (if TC-83 strain is used) or
to VEE, eastern equine encephalitis, and western equine encephalitis (if
the trivalent vaccine is used). This might put some of our younger readers
into shock but I recommend the complement-fixation (CF) test in such
situations. The trivalent vaccine contains killed viruses and does not
stimulate production of CF antibodies. TC-83 vaccine contains the live
attenuated virus but it does not stimulate production of CF antibodies. The
CF test is easy to do; I just do not know if there is still anyone alive
who uses it.
In addition, the trivalent vaccine does not stimulate production of IgM
antibody to any of the constituent viruses; the TC-83 vaccine does.
Finally, in a study published 20 years ago (Fillis, C.A. and C.H. Calisher.
Neutralizing antibody responses of humans and mice to vaccination with
Venezuelan encephalitis (TC-83) virus. J. Clin. Microbiol. 10:544-549,
1979), we showed that mice vaccinated with TC-83 (which is attenuated VEE
IAB) were susceptible to challenge with VEE ID, IE, II, III, and IV, and to
some extent to VEE IC. Humans vaccinated with TC-83 have high antibody
titer to VEE IAB, less to IC, and not much or none to the other subtypes.
Thus, TC-83 vaccine likely will not protect equids against any but VEE IAB
and maybe IC.
Clearly, the authorities in Honduras have applied coverage at a high level,
hence the limited outbreak and the absence of human cases. - Mod.CHC
